column1: # This file has a collection of transcription start sites (TSSs) that have been experimentally determined with high precision in Escherichia coli using
# a modified 5' RACE protocol (Mendoza-Vargas et al , 2009. PLoS One).
# From this collection, about 54 corresponded to previously reported TSSs, which helped us to benchmark both our methodologies and the accuracy of the previous mapping
# The TSSs mapped belong to about 269 different genes, many of them with no assigned function.
# Please when using this date quote:
# Alfredo Mendoza-Vargas(1), Leticia Olvera(1), Maricela Olvera(1), Ricardo Grande(4), Leticia Vega-Alvarado(2), Blanca Taboada(2), Verónica Jimenez-Jacinto(4),
# Heladia Salgado(3), Katy Juárez(1), Bruno Contreras-Moreira(3)€, Araceli M. Huerta(3), Julio Collado-Vides(3), Enrique Morett(1)*. 2009
# "Genome-Wide Identification of Transcription Start Sites, Promoters and Transcription Factor Binding Sites in E. coli".
#(1) Departamento de Ingeniería Celular y Biocatálisis, Instituto de Biotecnología, Universidad Nacional Autónoma de México, Cuernavaca, Morelos, México,
#(2) Centro de Ciencias Aplicadas y Desarrollo Tecnológico, Universidad Nacional Autónoma de México, Cuernavaca, Morelos, México,
#(3) Programa de Genómica Computacional, Centro de Ciencias Genómicas, Universidad Nacional Autónoma de México, Cuernavaca, Morelos, México,
#(4) Unidad Universitaria de Secuenciación Masiva, Universidad Nacional Autónoma de México, Cuernavaca, Morelos, México

column4: Directed Mapping of Transcriptional Start Sites (DMTSS) Data, divided in 3 sets:
Subset I:  With previously known TSS and  With promoter region predicted in this work
Subset II: Without previously known TSS and With promoter region predicted in this work
Subset III: Without previously known TSS and Without promoter region predicted in this work
Genome map position of Transcription Start Site (+1)
Frecuency: number of sequence in the same position
Sequence identifier assigned by Roche 454 GS Sequencer or assigned by authors
Genomic region where is located the TSS with respect to the nearest gene
Gene left end position in the genome
Gene rigth end position in the genome
DNA strand where the gene is coded
Sequence of the promoter region (+1 upper case)
